    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Windows formed by pieces of glass set into lead cames. While the glass may be colored, uncolored, or clear, the more specific "stained-glass windows" is typically used for windows in which all or most of the glass is colored.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
